"@johnsmorgan - Apologies for not responding here.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what exactly you mean here or how to devise a simple test case.\r\n\r\nAre you just suggesting to change the default for `bins=30` in\r\nhttp://iminuit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api.html#iminuit.Minuit.draw_mnprofile\r\nto e.g. `bins=31`? Would that help in your case?\n\nI think I understand the issue. Using uneven bin number may improve the situation but does not solve the underlying problem. The way how the contour plot is made is wrong. I need to have a closer look into draw_mnprofile to fix this properly. The MINOS algorithm is able to draw exact contours. We should not use these brittle approximations.\n\n@HDembinski - OK.\r\n\r\nBut there's a ton of methods to contour and parameters.\r\n\r\nAs always, my suggestion would be to mainly improve the docs, and refer them to scikit-image and MPL contouring, advertise these plot methods in iminuit only as quick-look.\n\nAnd as always, I don't want to be responsible for a software that gives such dangerously wrong results."